       "desc": "Midway decided to do something a little different with its Mortal Kombat franchise. They decided rather than to make a whole new MK game, they'd make a game that focused on one particular character from the popular series; a mini MK if you will. They'd shine some light on his past and present gamers with a story, rather than mindless fights to win a tournament. The character of choice is Sub Zero, and the game is aptly titled Mortal Kombat Mythologies: Sub Zero. \n Mythologies remains true to its parent series (up until Mortal Kombat 4, anyway) in a few aspects: all the characters are digitized and the game is still 2D. But unlike the other games in the series, this one's a platform adventure. You're not just fighting to win a tournament, you're fighting to find out the entire back story of Sub Zero. Sure, you'll still be beating up lots of bad guys, but the game is basically a \"jump from platform to platform\" game. Midway even throws in some RPG elements, such as item collection and a menu screen, to spice things up a bit. \n Features: \n * Explore eight distinct worlds while battling more than 30 enemies \n * Perform ice blasts, super slides, polar blasts, and more \n * Defeat a total of 12 boss characters, including Scorpion, Quan Chi, and Shinnok By Galisteo Games©",
